--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
= legend =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* `Mod`											Mod4 (Usually windows) key
	* `LC`											Left mouse click
	* `RC`											Right mouse click
	* `MC`											Middle mouse click
	* `MS`											Mouse scroll

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
= help =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* `Mod-alt-0`								Launch system help
	* `Mod-alt-1`								Launch vifm help

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
= general =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* `Mod-enter`								Launch terminal (`$TERMINAL`).
	* `Mod-q`										Close/kill window
	* `Mod-d`										Lauch app launcher (rofi)
	* `Mod-ctrl-shift-q`				Reload dwm
	* `Mod-z/Z`									Increase/decrease gaps May also hold `M-MS`
	* `Mod-a`										Toggle gaps
	* `Mod-shift-a`							Gaps to default values May also hold `M-MC`
	* `Mod-b`										Toggle statusbar 
	* `Mod-alt-shift-q`					Logout
	* `Mod-alt-ctrl-q`					shutdown
	* `Mod-alt-ctrl-shift-q`		reboot

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
= layouts =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* `Mod-t`										Tiling mode (active by default)
	* `Mod-shift-t`							Bottom stack mode (just like tiling, but master is on top)
	* `Mod-f`										Fullscreen mode
	* `Mod-shift-f`							Floating (AKA normie) mode
	* `Mod-y`										Fibbonacci spiral mode
	* `Mod-shift-y`							Dwindle mode (similar to Fibonacci)
	* `Mod-u`										Master on left, other windows in monocle mode
	* `Mod-shift-u`							Monocle mode (all windows fullscreen and cycle through)
	* `Mod-i`										Center master window
	* `Mod-shift-i`							Center and float master window
	* `Mod-o/O`									Increase/decrease the number of master windows

